The Pentagon confirmed that Manning was incarcerated in accordance with the regulations governing the conditions of detention of all detainees in Quantico.
The charges against Manning include theft of public goods or documents, collusion with the enemy, resulting in illegal publication of information on the Internet, and the transmission of national defence information.
If all indictments are held, he shall be liable to life imprisonment.
